.TH "D-Pad Store" "1" "" "Version 0.1.0" "D-Pad Store Manual Page Documentation"
.SH NAME
io.github.libredeb.dpad-store \- A full-screen kiosk-style game store
.SH SYNOPSIS
.PP
\f[B]io.github.libredeb.dpad-store\f[R] [ OPTION ] \&...
.SH DESCRIPTION
D-Pad Store is a visual wrapper over Pi-Apps scripts.
It provides a gamepad-navigable full-screen interface to browse and install
games from the Pi-Apps catalog.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
\-h, \-\-help
Show help options.
.TP
\-\-help\-all
Show all help options.
.TP
\-\-help\-gapplication
Show GApplication options.
.SH CONTROLS
.TP
\f[B]Gamepad / Joystick\f[R]
Navigate through the application list and select games to install.
.TP
\f[B]Escape\f[R]
Quit the application.
.SH PREREQUISITES
Pi-Apps must be installed in the user's home directory (~/.pi-apps).
See https://github.com/Botspot/pi-apps for installation instructions.
.SH FILES
.TP
\f[I]~/pi-apps/\f[R]
Pi-Apps installation directory, used to load available games and manage installations.
.TP
\f[I]~/pi-apps/data/status/\f[R]
Per-app status files used to determine installation state.
